The paper deals with optimizing data transfer protocols in a network environment, which is a core topic in computer networks (cs.NI). It also involves analyzing historical data and real-time traffic probing, which are techniques used in distributed computing (cs.DC) and data science (cs.DS). The optimization algorithms presented in the paper can be applied to a variety of systems, including scientific and commercial applications, which fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper also discusses the security implications of poorly tuned data transfer protocols, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR).
